    "summary": "I am inspired by nature and water since my childhood. As a senior consultant I am building bridges between people and organizations to make projects for water and nature work.\n\nI am working for 20 years as a landscape ecologist and project manager. I do so on a firm knowledge base of water resources management and nature conservation, spatial planning, process and project management and communication. Apart from this, I bring inspiration and commitment to the project and I think both aspects are vital for a good project. I am at my best in the early stages of a project; when ideas, people and finance need to be brought together in a joint ambition. \n\nI have worked the last years especially for water authorities, provinces and environmental NGO\u2019s; mostly in the Netherlands, but as well in Belgium, Spain, Bosnia, Romania, Austria, Bolivia and the United Kingdom. Some of the projects I recently worked on are:\n- Fish Migration River: innovative solution to soften negative ecological effects for migratory fish at the Afsluitdijk in the Netherlands\n- Natural Climate Buffer Oesterdam: pilot project for a climate proof dike based on eco engineering, combining investments in nature and improving safety in the Dutch Delta\n- Noordrand Goeree. Development of regional project for nature, housing and recreational development at the borders of the Haringvliet.\n\nSpecialties: Water management\nDelta management\nNature restoration\nProject development\nProcess management",
